# Delivery Verification

Before marking a coding task complete or handing changes to the user, run verification and fix failures first.

## Required commands

From the repo root:

```bash
bun run check
bun run typecheck
```

When changes are scoped to a single package, you may run filtered checks instead:

```bash
bun run --filter @jx3/api check
bun run --filter @jx3/api typecheck
```

Replace `@jx3/api` with the package you touched (`@jx3/web`, `@jx3/db`, etc.).

## When to run

- After implementing or modifying code
- Before saying work is done, tests pass, or a PR/commit is ready
- After fixing lint, format, or type errors reported by the user or CI

## On failure

- Fix Biome/format issues (`bun run fix` in the affected package, then re-run `check`)
- Fix TypeScript errors before delivery
- Do not claim completion without command output showing success

## Optional (when relevant)

- `bun run test` — when behavior changed or tests were added/updated
- `bun run --filter <package> test` — for package-scoped test runs
